						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is left unfinished. The details of date are given as Vṛiśchika, śu. 5, [Wednesday], Tiruvōṇam corresponding to A.D. 1008, November 6, Saturday (not Wednesday). On this date the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of the place and the <hi rend="italic">Sēnāpati</hi> (commander) Mummuḍiśōḻa-Brah[mārāyar] are said to have met in the temple at Pēriṅgūr (evidently for transacting some business).</p>						

